              I've seen many a fiasco get started because people at 64,000 feet high saw two similar applications and start thinking &quot;we should combine these&quot;.  Just because it sounds the same doesn't mean it is the same.<br /><br />By the time you get all the competing requirements settled out, two systems that would have cost $1 million apiece end up costing $10 million combined.

              

              
              
