              The F16 was the last planeproduced that was a win-win for the US and US taxpayers in terms of air superiority vs cost. The F-35, while a very cool plane, is not worth the cost. FYI on the F-16:<br /><br />&quot;In May 2013, Lockheed Martin stated it has enough orders to keep producing F-16s until 2017, with more orders possible.&quot;<br /><br />As for the F-35 &quot;In production with 1763 planned, currently 13 for testing&quot;<br /><br />You do the math as to how much 1763 of these planes will cost.

              

              
              
